    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In Christi nomine. Nos <persName key="#Princeps"
                            ref="#people/156 #people/167 #people/315">Landolfus</persName> divina
                        ordinante providentia <rs key="#Princeps">Langobardorum gentis
                        princeps</rs>, <rs key="#Intercessory">per rogum</rs>
                        <persName key="#brotherOf"><name ref="Aldemarus">Aldemari</name></persName>
                        e <persName key="#brotherOf"><name ref="Audoaldus"
                            >Audoaldi</name></persName> veris <rs key="#brotherOf">germanis</rs> et
                            <persName key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus"><name ref="Audoaldus"
                                >Adoaldi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Gastaldus/vicegastaldus">gastaldei</rs>
                        <rs key="#Personal_rank">dilecti</rs>
                        <rs key="#familyOf">parentes</rs> nostri, et mercede anime nostre,
                        concedimus in <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/84">Beati
                            Benedicti</orgName> quod constructum est in <rs key="#Castle"
                            >castro</rs> Casino, in quo domnus <persName key="#Abbots"
                            ref="#people/309">Aligernus</persName> venerabilis <rs key="#Abbots"
                            >abbas</rs> et spiritualis noster pater regimen tenere videtur,
                            <geogName key="#Petiae #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property"
                            ref="#estates/255">terra exfundatam</geogName> que <rs
                            key="#Petiae #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property">ad sacrum nostrum
                            Palatium pertinet</rs> intus <rs key="#Cities">civitate</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/111">vetere Telesie</placeName>, qui
                        coniuncta est cum <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs> eiusdem
                        monasterii in qua constructa est <rs key="#Churches">aecclesia Sancti
                            Domnini</rs> eiusdem monasterii pertinentem, et quibus eadem terra
                        videtur esse infra <rs key="#Confinia">fines</rs> haec et mensura: de capite
                        fine arcaturia qui descendit ad ipso <rs key="#Mills">molino</rs>
                        <persName key="#Count"><name ref="Landulfus">Landolfi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comitis</rs>
                        <rs key="#sonOf">filius</rs><persName><name ref="Rodelpotus">
                                Rodelpoti</name></persName>, ibidem sunt passi .X(m). et medium, de
                        latere fine <rs key="#Walls">muro</rs> ipsius civitatis a parte de ipso <rs
                            key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">pantano</rs>, ibidem per longitudinem
                        habet <rs key="#Size">passi</rs> XX et unum, de alio capite fine terra
                        monasterii <rs key="#Monasteries">Sancti Lupuli</rs>, ibidem sunt passi
                        X(m), de alio latere fine predicta <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Monasteries">terram eiusdem monasterii Sancti
                            Benedicti</rs> in qua predicta <rs key="#Churches">aecclesia Sancti
                            Domnini </rs>constructa est, ipsius monasterii pertinentem, ibidem per
                        longitudinem habet passi similiter XX et I. Per haec vero fines et mensura
                        eadem terra una cum inferius et cum sua pertinentia in integrum in prefato
                        sancto monasterio concedimus habendum, quatenus amodo et deinceps per hanc
                            <rs key="#Fiscal_property">nostram principalem concessionem</rs>
                        predicto venerabili loco eiusque rectoribus iam dictam terram <rs key="#Law"
                            >in suo iuris dominio</rs> in integrum habere et possidere debeant sine
                        ullius comitis, gastaldeis seu iudicibus nostris vel cuiuscumque persone
                        contrarietatem, facientes inde omnia quod voluerint, a nemine aliquod
                        contrarium in eodem sancto monasterio in aliquo ingerente. Scripsi
                            ego<persName
                            key="#Professional_writer #Notary #Clergy/religious_persons">
                            <name ref="Madelfridus">Madelfrid</name>
                        </persName><rs key="#Clergy/religious_persons">clericus</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Notary">notarius</rs> atque <rs key="#Professional_writer"
                            >scriba</rs> ex iussione supradicte potestatis in anno VI(o) principatus
                        superius dicti domini Landolfi gloriosi principis, mense Augusti, VIIII(a)
                        indictione. </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p>Voigt 1902, n. 162.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="additional">
                <p>Bloch 1986, pp. 735, 1347.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="links">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Il principe Landolfo (II, III o IV), su richiesta dei fratelli Aldemari e
                    Audoaldo e del gastaldo Audoaldo, suoi parenti, concede a Montecassino e
                    all’abate Aligerno un piccolo appezzamento di terra exfundata sito nella città
                    vecchia di Telese, a fianco della chiesa di S. Donnino sottoposta al monastero. </p>
            </div>
